<XMLDocContent PageName="cobalt.logging.ILogger.GetScope" Title="GetScope method" xmlns="http://www.cobaltrenderer.com/schema/XMLDocSchema.xsd">
  <Paragraph>
    <PageRef PageName="cobalt.logging.Welcome">Home</PageRef> ->
    <PageRef PageName="cobalt.logging.ILogger">ILogger</PageRef> ->
    GetScope
  </Paragraph>
  <Section Title="Description">
    <Paragraph>
      The <TypeRef>GetScope</TypeRef> method returns the scope string associated with the logger. Scopes are used by targets to identify which part of an application emitted a message.
    </Paragraph>
  </Section>
  <Section Title="Usage">
    <Code Language="C++"><![CDATA[std::string GetScope() const;]]></Code>
    <SubSection Title="Return value">
      <ReturnValue Type="std::string">
        The logger scope string.
      </ReturnValue>
    </SubSection>
  </Section>
